    public class Purchasable
extends java.lang.Object
implements android.os.Parcelable
    Represents an item that can be purchased. Encapsulates data about the purchase, such as a unique identifier.

      • Purchasable

        public Purchasable(java.lang.String productId,
           java.lang.String orderId)
        Constructs a new Purchasable
        Parameters:
        productId - An identifier for the product to be purchased. This is unique per-developer. Must not be null.
        orderId - A piece of information that the developer can choose to set. This is only used by the server to validate uniqueness of this transaction and will be returned in the server response to allow the developer to match purchase requests with purchase responses. Pass null in order to choose a random UUID value.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if an argument is null.
